    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, peel and and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a bowl with a small splash of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> <strong>petals</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Drain and add your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked through, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas</strong> with the <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the rice is hot</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>soy</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>oil</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>king prawn fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>king prawn fried rice</strong>, drizzle over the <strong>sriracha</strong> <strong>mayo </strong>and garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring</strong> <strong>onion</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> if needed</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave off the sriracha mayo and sliced spring onion, or just add a little!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
